# Development Workflow

## Available Scripts
The following npm scripts are available (defined in [package.json](mdc:package.json)):

- `npm run dev` - Start development server
- `npm run build` - Build for production
- `npm run preview` - Preview production build
- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint

## TypeScript Configuration
The project uses a multi-tsconfig setup:
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - Base TypeScript configuration
- [tsconfig.app.json](mdc:tsconfig.app.json) - App-specific configuration
- [tsconfig.node.json](mdc:tsconfig.node.json) - Node.js specific configuration

## Code Quality
ESLint is configured in [eslint.config.js](mdc:eslint.config.js) with modern React best practices including:
- React Hooks rules
- React Refresh
- TypeScript-specific rules
